OL,3,CBurnham's Makerfield by-election win
OL,4,Cspells end for Starmer as prime
OL,5,Cminister
OL,7,FThe Makerfield by-election spells the
OL,8,Fend for Keir Starmer as prime minister.
OL,10,FHow and when he leaves office is still
OL,11,Fto be determined, but Andy Burnham has
OL,12,Fall the momentum and Keir Starmer has
OL,13,Falmost nothing to stop him.
OL,15,FAndy Burnham almost doubled Labour's
OL,16,Fmajority in one of Reform's top target
OL,17,Fseats; he has united almost all of the
OL,18,F'progressive' vote behind him in
OL,19,FMakerfield and he has shown a way for
OL,20,FLabour to win again when many in the
OL,21,Fparty feared an existential wipeout.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
